> since streams is already depending on slf4j whats the motivation behind not just using slf4j for output instead of manually handling System.out and other PrintStreams.

@norwood , @guozhangwang 

What about keeping print() to System.out, but adding a print(Logger log) method that writes results to the given logger (log file)

@ewencp Running the sanity check test in a loop of 100 iterations here:

https://jenkins.confluent.io/job/system-test-kafka-branch-builder-2/49/consoleFull

So far, 20 iterations passed.

Comments addressed from closed PR #1187 

> @bbejeck @norwood The problem with using a given logger is that the logging level is universal, and hence users either 1) use a separate logger which is not used anywhere else, and set in log4j.properties the logging level for this specific logger, or 2) use a shared logger and tolerate it outputs other entries with the same logging level. Hence I'd prefer keep the current APIs and add the log4j support for print when we see common usage that requires it.

@guozhangwang  - Agreed left the print/write functions as is.

> @bbejeck I have modified the behavior of MockProcessorContext in #1204, would that help your unit tests?

@guozhangwang yes that works fine.  Should I revert my change to MockProcessorContext and re-push?

Edit: NM that wouldn't work as the test would fail. When #1204 is merged into trunk,  I can rebase this PR.

@WarrenGreen sorry it has taken so long to get this in. The following commit changes some of the underlying code that `AdminClient` relies on:

https://github.com/apache/kafka/commit/9c34df1511a769b272893b75ec1ed90d38cc9576

It also seemed to have caused some conflicts. Can you please merge trunk into your branch?
